can combine inference rules with unification to prove or infer things.

1.for all X (human(X) => has_2_legs(X)).

in prolog code
has_2_legs(X) :-
	human(X).

2. human(john).

unify x/john in rule to get
3. human(john) => has_2_legs(john).

using modus ponnens on 2 & 3

